      "message": "Use constants from PolicyProperties in case the naming convention is changed, so this does not break.   See PolicyEngineManager.defaultTelemetryConfig as a reference.\n\nIn general, you can set appropriate default values and avoid the \"if\" statements below (which should not be throwing generic exceptions), for example:\n\n\tString testHost = stateManagementProperties.getProperty(\"http.server.services.TEST.host\", \"0.0.0.0\");\n\tString testPort = stateManagementProperties.getProperty(\"http.server.services.TEST.port\", 1234);\n\tString testRestClasses = stateManagementProperties.getProperty(\"http.server.services.TEST.restClasses\", \"xxx\");\n....",
